      <section eId="sec_125_20">
        <num>125.20</num>
        <heading>Manslaughter in the first degree</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_125_20__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of subdivision one of\nsection 125.25. The fact that homicide was committed under the influence\nof extreme emotional disturbance constitutes a mitigating circumstance\nreducing murder to manslaughter in the first degree and need not be\nproved in any prosecution initiated under this subdivision; or\n  4. Being eighteen years old or more and with intent to cause physical\ninjury to a person less than eleven years old, the defendant recklessly\nengages in conduct which creates a grave risk of serious physical injury\nto such person and thereby causes the death of such person.\n  Manslaughter in the first degree is a class B felony.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
